description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced and enthusiastic General Practitioner&#39;s to join our Emergency Department at St. Helier Hospital. The role is part of a team working with nurses, doctors and administrative staff. The key working relationships are with the lead EM consultant, GP Lead, streaming nurses and receptionist staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for the delivery of high-quality streaming services at St Helier Hospital. The GP will deliver care of the highest clinical standards and will work in conjunction with the Triage nurse and a receptionist to ensure effective overall performance of the Emergency department. At all times the post holder will act in a manner consistent with the GMC’s Good Medical Practice and St Helier Hospital’s values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Shifts are available between 9am and 11pm 7 days per week and usually split into two shifts – 9am to 6pm 6pm to 11pm&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview: TBC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAmir HassanJob titleClinical DirectorEmail addressamir.hassan@nhs.netTelephone number0208 296 2000Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
